<p> Government refutes claim the elderly will pay £60,000 for care </p>
<p> Care minister Paul Burstow says decision on how much the elderly or disabled must pay themselves will not be made until spring </p>
<p> Tweet this </p>
<p> reddit this </p>
<p> omnitracker.omniTrackEVarEvent( 12, 16, 'Social care network: Reddit', 'click', '.reddit a' ); </p>
